comments.body:
> Note that, similarly, custom widths in later columns only take effect if one was specified for and successfully applied to the first column - except, seemingly, for the last column, for which a custom width is seemingly always ignored.

I can't repro the bug for the last column, e. g. this test succeeds (PS 7.1 and 7.2.0-preview.2):

    $obj = [pscustomobject]@{ a = '123456'; b = '123456'; c = '123456' } 
    $table = $obj | Format-Table -Property @{ e='a'; width=5 }, @{ e='b'; width=5 }, @{ e='c'; width=5 }
    $table | Out-String | Should -Match '1234… 1234… 1234…'

There is a typo in the title of this issue: "Formate-Table" -> "Format-Table"
